CommonFields.Title: Morphology, mechanical properties and thermal degradation kinetics of PMMA-zirconia nanocomposites prepared by melt compounding
Author: Motaung, T. E.
Luyt, A. S.
Saladino, M. L.
Martino, D. C.
Caponetti, E.
CommonFields.Publisher: Budapest University of Technology and Economics, Dept. of Polymer Engineering

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The polymer was dried at 120°C overnight under static vacuum before processing.

Mixing.Description: The PMMA pellets were thoroughly mixed for 10 min at 200°C and 30 rpm in a 50 mL internal mixer of a Brabender Plastograph.
Mixing.Mixer: internal mixer of a Brabender Plastograph

MoldingInfo.Description: The mixed samples were melt-pressed into 1 mm thick sheets at 200°C for 5 min.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: TEM micrographs were acquired by using a JEM- 2100 (JEOL, Japan) electron microscope operating at 200 kV accelerating voltage equipped with an Xray energy dispersive spectrometer (EDS, Oxford, model INCA ENERGY-200T) for analysis of elements.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: The dynamic mechanical analysis (DMA) of the blends and composites was performed from 40 to 180ºC in the bending mode at a heating rate of 5ºC min–1 and a frequency of 1 Hz.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: The analyses were done under flowing nitrogen at a constant flow rate of 20 mL min–1. Samples (20– 25 mg) were heated from 30 to 600°C at 10°C min–1 and held for 4 min at 600°C.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: XRD patterns were recorded in the 2–70° 2-theta range at steps of 0.05° and a counting time of 5 s/step on a Philips PW 1050 diffractometer, equipped with a Cu tube and a scintillation detector beam.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The analyses were done under flowing nitrogen at a constant flow rate of 20 mL min–1. Samples (5–10 mg) were heated from 25 to 600°C at different heating rates.

Nuclear_Magnetic_Resonance.Equipment: Bruker Avance II 400 MHz (9.4 T) spectrometer
